This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as consensus maximization is a widely used robust fitting paradigm in computer vision. The paper also proposes an efficient deterministic optimization algorithm for consensus maximization, which is a common problem in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as the proposed algorithm involves optimization and improving the quality of the initial solution. 

The paper may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a novel biconvex optimization algorithm. 

The paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as consensus maximization is a common problem in AI applications such as robotics and autonomous systems. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category as it proposes an optimization algorithm for solving biconvex programming instances.
